After the initial hesitancy, Kenyans are steadily embracing Covid-19 vaccines going by the huge number of people lining up daily outside health institutions that are offering vaccination.  While that is encouraging, security agencies in conjunction with health authorities must do everything to stop wily individuals from taking advantage of desperate Kenyans seeking vaccination.  There are reports that some people are minting money out of the exercise by arriving early and booking vaccination slots which they then hawk to those who arrive later. Help us serve you better by completing our quick survey. Such people who have no intention of being vaccinated, or have already been vaccinated should be kept out the precincts of the health facilities. Needless to say, their actions are denying people, who have no money to bribe them or who are averse to corruption, an opportunity to be vaccinated. Busybodies should not be allowed to determine who gets immunised.  Why Kenya should avoid a fourth Covid wave at all cost  Is it okay to allow matatus to carry at full capacity?  It's not yet time for PSVs to go back to normal  Why youth are avoiding Covid-19 jab     Government sets aside Ksh 7 billion for vaccines to acquire two different types of Covid-19 vaccines By Editorial | 7 hours ago By Editorial | 4 days ago By Editorial | 8 days ago By Editorial | 8 days ago